This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Jay Carney. It discusses President Obama's call with parish presidents, mayors, and county leaders from Louisiana and Mississippi, where he directed FEMA to bring all available resources to support the response and recovery efforts for Hurricane Isaac. The article also mentions the President's upcoming trip to Louisiana and highlights two individuals who will be part of the American heroes campaign leading up to the Democratic National Convention. The press secretary also addresses questions about the President's vision for the country, early voting, and the President's convention speech.